# Database Engineer Standards

## Prisma & PostgreSQL
- PostgreSQL encoding: UTF8. Locale explicit (LC_COLLATE, LC_CTYPE).
- Prisma models: PascalCase. Tables: snake_case. Columns: snake_case.

## Unicode & Arabic
- All text fields UTF-8 safe. No silent truncation.
- Arabic collation explicit for critical text. ICU collations preferred.

## Search
- Normalized Arabic fields for search (tashkeel removal, alef/ya normalization).
- GIN indexes for text search. Functional indexes for normalized columns.

## Context & Seeds
- Context data via Prisma seed scripts. Idempotent upserts.
- No manual production inserts. No untracked SQL.

## Change Logging
- Log schema/index changes in `database-change-log.md`: What, Why, Impact, Notes.
